        <p>Bruce Lee was a legendary martial artist, actor, and filmmaker. He was born in San Francisco, California, but raised in Hong Kong. Bruce Lee is widely regarded as one of the most influential martial artists of all time and played a key role in popularizing martial arts worldwide.</p>
        <p>Lee began studying martial arts at a young age and developed his own martial arts philosophy known as Jeet Kune Do. He is best known for his exceptional skills in martial arts, particularly in Wing Chun Kung Fu and later incorporating elements from various other disciplines.</p>
        <p>In addition to his martial arts prowess, Bruce Lee became a successful actor. He starred in a series of Hong Kong martial arts films, including "The Big Boss," "Fist of Fury," "Way of the Dragon," and "Enter the Dragon." "Enter the Dragon" was released shortly after his death and became a major success, solidifying his legacy as a martial arts icon.</p>
        <p>Bruce Lee's impact on martial arts and popular culture continues to be profound, and he is remembered as a symbol of martial arts excellence, philosophy, and breaking cultural barriers in the film industry.</p>
